-- Nets Defeat Bulls 106-89 to Take 1-0 Lead in NBA Playoff Series
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-04-21T02:37:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-21/nets-defeat-bulls-106-89-to-take-1-0-lead-in-nba-playoff-series.html
The Brooklyn Nets defeated the
Chicago Bulls 106-89 to take a 1-0 lead in their National
Basketball Association Eastern Conference best-of-seven playoff
series.  Deron Williams had 22 points and Brook Lopez scored 21
points for the Nets, who had a 60-35 halftime lead on their home
court at Barclays Center.  Carlos Boozer  had 25 points for the Bulls, who trailed by as
many as 28 points in the third quarter.  The Nets host Game 2 of the series on April 22.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nancy Kercheval at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net  